// ETS 기출 RC Test1 (Part5·6·7)
window.ETS_RC1 = {"p5": [{"n": 101, "en": "The lecture will take place at 6:00 P.M., ______ which attendees may ask questions.", "opts": ["across", "after", "inside", "among"], "ans": 1, "ko": "강연은 오후 6시에 열리며, 그 후 참석자들은 질문을 할 수 있습니다.", "note": "선행사 6:00 P.M.을 받는 관계대명사 which와 결합해 '~ 후에'를 뜻하는 전치사 after가 정답."}, {"n": 102, "en": "The ______ antique shop in Pepper Valley will close down next month.", "opts": ["last", "lasts", "lasted", "lasting"], "ans": 0, "ko": "페퍼 밸리에 있는 마지막 골동품 가게가 다음 달에 문을 닫을 예정이다.", "note": "정관사 the와 명사구 사이 명사 수식 형용사 자리로 '마지막'을 뜻하는 last가 정답."}, {"n": 103, "en": "Merryville residents will receive an online status ______ about the ongoing bridge construction project.", "opts": ["update", "change", "payment", "request"], "ans": 0, "ko": "메리빌 주민들은 진행 중인 다리 건설 프로젝트에 대해 온라인 현황 업데이트를 받을 것이다.", "note": "형용사 online의 수식을 받으며 status와 복합명사를 이루는 update가 정답."}, {"n": 104, "en": "As a result of ______ many years leading media organizations, Ms. Ayo was selected for the Dowel Journalism Prize.", "opts": ["she", "her", "hers", "herself"], "ans": 1, "ko": "다년간 언론 단체를 이끌어 온 결과, 야오 씨는 도월 언론상의 수상자로 선정되었다.", "note": "명사구 many years를 수식하는 한정사 역할의 소유격 인칭대명사 her가 정답."}, {"n": 105, "en": "To stop the ______ of computer viruses, do not open suspicious e-mails.", "opts": ["break", "spread", "balance", "surface"], "ans": 1, "ko": "컴퓨터 바이러스의 확산을 막기 위해 의심스러운 이메일은 열지 마십시오.", "note": "to부정사 To stop의 목적어 명사 자리로 '확산'을 뜻하는 spread가 정답."}, {"n": 106, "en": "The hiring manager ______ considered each applicant's résumé and qualifications.", "opts": ["caring", "careful", "carefully", "carefulness"], "ans": 2, "ko": "채용 관리자는 각 지원자의 이력서와 자격을 면밀히 검토했다.", "note": "주어와 동사 사이에서 동사를 수식하는 부사 자리로 '면밀히'를 뜻하는 carefully가 정답."}, {"n": 107, "en": "In October, Mr. Sakamoto will leave for New Zealand ______ will oversee the opening of the new Auckland branch.", "opts": ["because", "in addition", "and", "prior to"], "ans": 2, "ko": "", "note": "완전한 절 앞뒤로 절이 이어지므로 등위접속사 and가 정답 (해설이 페이지에서 잘림)."}, {"n": 108, "en": "Tarateer Pharmaceuticals is varying its product ______ to include over-the-counter medications.", "opts": ["to line", "lining", "lined", "line"], "ans": 3, "ko": "타리티어 제약 회사는 일반 의약품을 포함할 수 있도록 제품군을 다양화하고 있다.", "note": "동사 is varying의 목적어 자리이자 앞의 product와 복합명사를 이루는 명사 (D) line이 정답."}, {"n": 109, "en": "Dynart, Inc., continuously ______ new ways to reduce its use of plastics.", "opts": ["seeks", "seeker", "to seek", "seeking"], "ans": 0, "ko": "다이너트 사는 플라스틱 사용을 줄이기 위한 새로운 방법을 지속적으로 찾고 있다.", "note": "문장에 동사가 없으므로 동사 자리, '찾다'를 뜻하는 (A) seeks가 정답."}, {"n": 110, "en": "The cash registers at Pirkle Books automatically ______ the remaining inventory of books available.", "opts": ["calculate", "calculator", "calculating", "calculation"], "ans": 0, "ko": "퍼플 북스의 계산대는 구매 가능한 남은 도서 재고를 자동으로 산출한다.", "note": "문장에 동사가 없으므로 동사 자리, '산출하다'를 뜻하는 (A) calculate가 정답."}, {"n": 111, "en": "The product team is designing mapping software that can ______ locate underground minerals.", "opts": ["infinitely", "sincerely", "precisely", "greatly"], "ans": 2, "ko": "제품 팀은 지하 광물의 위치를 정확하게 찾아낼 수 있는 지도 소프트웨어를 설계 중이다.", "note": "조동사 can과 동사원형 locate 사이 동사를 수식하는 부사 자리, '정확하게'를 뜻하는 (C) precisely가 정답."}, {"n": 112, "en": "According to CEO Mayu Yamada, it would not be ______ responsible to expand the warehouse at this time.", "opts": ["finance", "financials", "financially", "financing"], "ans": 2, "ko": "마유 야마다 CEO에 따르면, 현시점에 창고를 확장하는 것은 재정적으로 무책임한 일일 것이다.", "note": "형용사 responsible을 수식하는 부사 자리, '재정적으로'를 뜻하는 (C) financially가 정답."}, {"n": 113, "en": "Analysts cannot say with any ______ what the regional demand for electric trucks will be.", "opts": ["certainty", "justice", "excellence", "denial"], "ans": 0, "ko": "분석가들은 전기 트럭에 대한 지역별 수요가 얼마나 될지 확실하게 말할 수 없다.", "note": "with any와 결합해 '어떠한 확신도 없다'는 문맥, '확신·확실성'을 뜻하는 (A) certainty가 정답."}, {"n": 114, "en": "As part of its marketing campaign, Elegancia Dishware is ______ soliciting feedback from customers.", "opts": ["lightly", "loyally", "actively", "cleanly"], "ans": 2, "ko": "엘레강시아 식기는 마케팅 캠페인의 일환으로 고객으로부터 의견을 적극적으로 요청하고 있다.", "note": "동사 is soliciting을 수식해 '적극적으로 요청하다'는 문맥, '적극적으로'를 뜻하는 (C) actively가 정답."}, {"n": 115, "en": "Rain gardens are intended to ______ water to prevent flooding of local roads.", "opts": ["engage", "undergo", "absorb", "overwhelm"], "ans": 1, "ko": "빗물 정원은 지역 도로의 침수를 예방하기 위해 물을 흡수하도록 설계되었다.", "note": "be intended+to부정사 구조에서 water를 목적어로 '흡수하다'를 뜻하는 (C) absorb가 정답."}, {"n": 116, "en": "Theta Industries' training program aims to increase the ______ of its manufacturing systems.", "opts": ["producer", "produced", "productive", "productivity"], "ans": 2, "ko": "세타 산업의 교육 프로그램은 제조 시스템의 생산성을 향상시키는 것을 목표로 한다.", "note": "정관사 the와 전치사 of 사이, to increase의 목적어 자리이므로 명사 productivity."}, {"n": 117, "en": "The board of directors has voted to award Mr. Mitrakos a bonus for his role ______ obtaining the international contract.", "opts": ["in", "at", "except", "apart"], "ans": 0, "ko": "이사회는 미트라코스 씨에게 국제 계약을 따내는 데 있어서 그가 한 역할에 대해 보너스를 지급하기로 의결했다.", "note": "뒤의 동명사 obtaining과 결합해 '획득하는 데 있어서의 역할' 의미이므로 전치사 in."}, {"n": 118, "en": "The finance director gave his approval ______ the project can move forward.", "opts": ["along", "furthermore", "cautiously", "so that"], "ans": 2, "ko": "재무 이사는 프로젝트가 진행될 수 있도록 승인해 주었다.", "note": "두 완전한 절을 이어주는 부사절 접속사 자리이므로 so that."}, {"n": 119, "en": "The newspaper article describes ways job seekers can ______ for having little workplace experience.", "opts": ["reply", "capture", "compensate", "accumulate"], "ans": 2, "ko": "그 신문 기사는 구직자들이 직장 경력이 부족한 것을 보완할 수 있는 방법을 설명한다.", "note": "뒤 for와 연결되는 자동사, '~을 보완하다' 의미의 compensate."}, {"n": 120, "en": "Mr. Ellis and Ms. Barnes were both highly qualified, but ______ got the job.", "opts": ["myself", "neither", "anybody", "whoever"], "ans": 1, "ko": "엘리스 씨와 반즈 씨 모두 자격이 충분히 있었지만 둘 다 일자리를 얻지는 못했다.", "note": "but절 동사 got의 주어 자리, '둘 중 누구도 아니다' 의미의 부정대명사 neither."}, {"n": 121, "en": "Ennis Photography purchased all new lighting equipment ______ the high cost.", "opts": ["even though", "however", "until", "despite"], "ans": 0, "ko": "에니스 사진은 높은 비용에도 불구하고 모든 새로운 조명 장비를 구입했다.", "note": "완전한 절 뒤 명사구 앞, '~에도 불구하고' 의미의 전치사 despite."}, {"n": 122, "en": "Marburton residents who wish to ______ a home should contact the award-winning team at Kwan Real Estate.", "opts": ["seller", "sold", "sell", "selling"], "ans": 2, "ko": "주택을 판매하고자 하는 마버턴 주민은 콴 부동산의 수상 경력이 있는 팀에 연락해야 한다.", "note": "동사 wish의 목적어 to부정사의 동사원형 자리이므로 sell."}, {"n": 123, "en": "Maswa Bistro began a ______ agreement with local farmers to purchase a set amount of produce each week.", "opts": ["disruptive", "cooperative", "grateful", "concerned"], "ans": 1, "ko": "마스와 비스트로는 지역 농민들과 매주 일정량의 농산물을 구매하는 협력적인 계약을 시작했다.", "note": "명사 agreement를 수식해 '협력적인' 의미가 되어야 하므로 cooperative."}, {"n": 124, "en": "The City of Doyle's new downtown parking ______ have been met with opposition by residents and visitors.", "opts": ["restricts", "restricted", "restrictions", "restricting"], "ans": 2, "ko": "", "note": ""}, {"n": 125, "en": "The plumbing position requires extensive training, even for those who studied ______ in technical school.", "opts": ["diligently", "scientifically", "objectively", "decidedly"], "ans": 1, "ko": "", "note": ""}, {"n": 126, "en": "With its fixed price ______, Omega Cellular guarantees no phone bill increases for three years.", "opts": ["assurance", "assuredly", "assuring", "assures"], "ans": 0, "ko": "", "note": ""}, {"n": 127, "en": "As chief analytics officer, Mr. Ko has worked at Lochston Ltd. with great ______ for more than twenty years.", "opts": ["deduction", "duplication", "declaration", "dedication"], "ans": 3, "ko": "", "note": ""}, {"n": 128, "en": "Milltown Hospital's cafeteria serves lunch seven days a week ______ only on weekdays.", "opts": ["up to", "as though", "each time", "rather than"], "ans": 2, "ko": "", "note": ""}, {"n": 129, "en": "The store's entire inventory of lumber comes from a nearby ______ supplier.", "opts": ["financial", "promotional", "chemical", "commercial"], "ans": 3, "ko": "", "note": ""}, {"n": 130, "en": "For a $95 ______ fee, our mechanics will determine what repairs are needed.", "opts": ["diagnosed", "diagnostic", "diagnosable", "diagnose"], "ans": 1, "ko": "", "note": ""}], "p6": [{"title": "Questions 131-134 refer to the following flyer.", "text": "Look to Riessler Landscaping for your Garden Needs\n\nRiessler Landscaping has everything you need to create your dream garden. We will listen to your ideas and offer suggestions that match your gardening desires. (131)______ . The nursery here at Riessler Landscaping includes plants of many varieties and sizes that burst with eye-catching colors year-round. You are guaranteed to find something that will add (132)______ to your garden. We are (133)______ equipped to construct small ponds or other water features. And as our name suggests, we can take on more ambitious landscaping projects—whatever you need! With more than 40 years in the landscape–design business, (134)______ expertise is unmatched.", "qs": [{"n": 131, "opts": ["Staff members have written articles for the local newspaper.", "Installing lights can enhance the effect of a well-designed garden.", "Local competitors cannot beat the prices we charge.", "Riessler Landscaping's goal is to make your vision a reality."], "ans": 3, "note": "빈칸 앞은 고객 아이디어를 경청하고 제안을 해준다는 내용, 뒤는 고객 정원을 실현하려 리슬러 조경이 서비스를 제공한다는 내용이므로, 두 내용을 연결하는 '리슬러 조경의 목표는 귀하의 상상을 현실로 만드는 것'이라는 (D)가 정답."}, {"n": 132, "opts": ["years", "space", "beauty", "moisture"], "ans": 2, "note": "묘목장에 눈길을 사로잡는 색으로 가득한 다양한 품종과 크기의 식물을 보유하고 있다는 내용이므로 '아름다움'을 뜻하는 (C) beauty가 정답."}, {"n": 133, "opts": ["also", "rarely", "somehow", "nevertheless"], "ans": 0, "note": "식물 판매 외에 수경 시설 시공 장비도 갖추고 서비스를 추가로 소개하고 있으므로 '또한'이라는 뜻의 (A) also가 정답."}, {"n": 134, "opts": ["its", "our", "others", "their"], "ans": 1, "note": "명사 expertise를 한정 수식하는 자리로 소유격 대명사가 들어가야 하며, 보의 주체 리슬러 조경을 'We/our'로 지칭하므로 '저희의 전문성'이 적합해 (B) our가 정답."}]}, {"title": "Questions 135-138 refer to the following letter.", "text": "10 January\n\nCindy Mulligan\n88 Manchester Road\nHARROGATE\nHG82 2MJ\n\nDear Ms. Mulligan,\n\nWe are delighted to celebrate your 30th anniversary with Brandrix Distribution Centre. (135)______ . Your dedication, loyalty, and hard work have contributed greatly to our success over the years. We appreciate your commitment to excellence. Over the years, you (136)______ great initiative, creativity, and leadership.\n\nYou will (137)______ be receiving a commemorative plaque by post. We hope this token of our gratitude reminds you how much you mean to us.\n\nCongratulations on reaching this (138)______ . Thank you for being part of our Brandrix family.\n\nSincerely,\n\nLance Powar, Vice President of Human Resources\nBrandrix Distribution Centre", "qs": [{"n": 135, "opts": ["We especially value our long-term customers.", "Please join our holiday celebration.", "Our annual report will be released soon.", "You have been a valuable member of our team."], "ans": 3, "note": "빈칸 앞은 브랜드릭스 유통 센터와 함께한 30주년을 기념한다는 내용, 뒤는 귀하의 헌신·충성심·노고가 성공에 크게 기여했다는 내용이므로 함께 근무한 동료로서 가치를 인정하는 '당신은 우리 팀의 소중한 구성원이었다'는 (D)가 정답."}, {"n": 136, "opts": ["will show", "must show", "have shown", "are showing"], "ans": 2, "note": "동사 시제 문제. over the years가 단서로, 과거부터 현재까지 계속된 행위는 현재완료 시제를 써야 하므로 (C) have shown이 정답."}, {"n": 137, "opts": ["then", "soon", "instead", "likewise"], "ans": 1, "note": "부사 어휘. 미래 시제 조동사 will과 어울려 '곧 기념패를 받게 될 것'이라는 의미가 되어야 하므로 '곧'을 뜻하는 (B) soon이 정답."}, {"n": 138, "opts": ["milestone", "consensus", "destination", "understanding"], "ans": 0, "note": "명사 어휘. 브랜드릭스 유통 센터와 함께한 30주년을 기념한다는 맥락으로 '30년'이라는 이정표에 도달한 것을 축하하므로 '이정표'를 뜻하는 (A) milestone이 정답."}]}, {"title": "Questions 139-142 refer to the following e-mail.", "text": "To: Kay Berman <kberman@xmail.com>\nFrom: Ali Chaleby <achaleby@ralenciadesign.com>\nDate: August 21\nSubject: Plans for living room\nAttachment: Samples\n\nDear Ms. Berman,\n\nMy design team is in the process of (139)______ the plans for your living room. Based on our last conversation, I have chosen different paints for the walls and borders. Please review the attached file and decide whether you like those new (140)______ . If not, it is not too late to make a change. (141)______ . Your review will help us refine the design before we start.\n\nPlease let (142)______ know if you have any questions. I look forward to hearing from you.\n\nKind regards,\n\nAli Chaleby, Ralencia Design", "qs": [{"n": 139, "opts": ["finalizing", "finalize", "finalized", "finalizes"], "ans": 0, "note": "동명사/전치사의 목적어. 전치사 of의 목적어 역할을 하며 뒤의 명사 the plans를 목적어로 취할 수 있는 동명사가 필요하므로 (A) finalizing이 정답."}, {"n": 140, "opts": ["organizations", "schedules", "colors", "times"], "ans": 2, "note": "명사 어휘. 지난번 대화를 바탕으로 벽과 테두리에 다른 페인트를 선택했으니 이 새로운 색상이 마음에 드는지 결정해 달라는 내용이므로 '색상'을 뜻하는 (C) colors가 정답."}, {"n": 141, "opts": ["I have already begun drawing up plans for your kitchen.", "We are not planning to begin work for another two weeks.", "Your living room is particularly spacious and airy.", "We have not yet received your current payment."], "ans": 1, "note": "문맥에 맞는 문장 고르기. 앞·뒤 문장이 공사 시작 전에 시간이 남아 있음을 알리는 흐름이므로 '앞으로 2주간은 공사를 시작할 계획이 없습니다'라는 (B)가 정답."}, {"n": 142, "opts": ["them", "ours", "his", "me"], "ans": 3, "note": "대명사 어휘. 뒤 문장에서 귀하의 답변을 기다리겠다고 했으므로 '문의 사항이 있으면 저에게 알려 달라'는 내용이 적절하여 (D) me가 정답."}]}, {"title": "Questions 143-146 refer to the following e-mail.", "text": "To: Marsha Zalen <mzalen@mansfield.com>\nFrom: Kaymar PCP <info@kaymarpcp.com>\nDate: September 8\nSubject: Your recent office visit\n\nDear Ms. Zalen,\n\nThank you for your recent visit to Kaymar Primary Care Practice. We hope you found our services (143)______ , and we welcome suggestions for improvement.\n\nWe have posted a (144)______ of your consultation on our portal. Please take a moment to go through it and let us know if you have any questions.\n\nAs a reminder, you can log in to the portal for various activities. (145)______ , you can make appointments and payments, view your medical history, review lab results, and request medication refills. (146)______ . Rest assured that your personal information is safe and secure.\n\nWe thank you for your business and look forward to serving you again.\n\nKaymar Primary Care Practice", "qs": [{"n": 143, "opts": ["satisfied", "satisfaction", "satisfactory", "satisfactorily"], "ans": 2, "note": "빈칸은 동사 hope의 목적어 역할을 하는 명사절에서 5형식 동사 found의 목적격 보어 자리. our services를 수식해 '우리 서비스를 만족스럽게 여기기를 바란다'는 뜻이 되어야 하므로 '만족스러운'을 뜻하는 (C) satisfactory가 정답."}, {"n": 144, "opts": ["photo", "lecture", "summary", "schedule"], "ans": 2, "note": "케이마르 1차 진료소를 최근 방문해 감사하다고 했고 빈칸 뒤 검토해 질문 있으면 알려달라 했으므로, 진료 요약 서류임을 알 수 있어 '요약'을 뜻하는 (C) summary가 정답."}, {"n": 145, "opts": ["To repeat", "For instance", "Otherwise", "Consequently"], "ans": 1, "note": "앞 문장의 다양한 활동을 위해 포털에 로그인할 수 있다는 내용 뒤에 예약·결제·기록 조회 등 예시를 구체적으로 나열하므로 '예를 들어'를 뜻하는 (B) For instance가 정답."}, {"n": 146, "opts": ["We hope you will use this resource to manage your health-care needs.", "The staff will close the office early on Friday afternoons.", "Please be sure to come to our office fifteen minutes in advance.", "We apologize for any confusion about your appointment time."], "ans": 0, "note": "빈칸 앞에서 포털 로그인 시 예약·결제·기록 조회·재처방 요청 등 다양한 활동을 소개하고 있으므로, 포털 사용을 장려하는 '건강 관리에 필요한 사항들을 관리하는 데 이 방편을 활용하시기 바랍니다'라는 (A)가 정답."}]}], "p7": [{"title": "Questions 147-148 refer to the following notice.", "passage": "Dear High View Apartments Resident,\n\nRiverside Paving Company is coming to High View Apartments on May 3 and 4 to resurface the parking area. All vehicles must be removed by 8 A.M. on May 3 for the work to commence. Residents may use the parking area again starting on May 5 at 8 A.M. We realize that trying to find another place to park is inconvenient, but it is necessary for the job to be completed in the two days scheduled. Note that all parking spaces will be widened, and some spaces could be moved during the work. You will receive an e-mail if your parking space is moved more than 20 meters from your previous one.\n\nThank you for your cooperation,\nJudith Alvarez, Property Manager", "qs": [{"n": 147, "q": "What is the purpose of the notice?", "opts": ["To invite residents to a meeting on May 3", "To request feedback about parking facilities", "To inform residents of an upcoming project", "To announce an increase in parking fees"], "ans": 2, "note": "공지의 목적을 묻는 문제. 첫 문장에서 리버사이드 포장 회사가 5월 3~4일 하이 뷰 아파트에 와서 주차 구역을 재포장한다고 알리고 있으므로, 다가오는 공사에 대해 주민들에게 알리려는 (C)가 정답."}, {"n": 148, "q": "What is suggested about High View Apartments?", "opts": ["It charges residents a monthly maintenance fee.", "It recently hired a new property manager.", "It has the parking area repaved every year.", "It assigns tenants specific parking spots."], "ans": 3, "note": "하이 뷰 아파트에 대해 암시된 것: 주차 공간이 기존 위치에서 20m 이상 이동되면 이메일을 받는다고 했으므로, 세입자들에게 특정 주차 공간을 배정해 준다는 것을 유추할 수 있다. 정답 (D)."}]}, {"title": "Questions 149-150 refer to the following text-message chain.", "passage": "Carol Barger (10:45 A.M.)\nHello, Ms. Seang.\n\nLeakhena Seang (10:55 A.M.)\nGood morning!\n\nCarol Barger (11:15 A.M.)\nWe have fifteen participants enrolled in your mosaic workshop tomorrow. That is five more than last summer. Your workshops get more popular every year! Do you have enough materials on hand for that many participants?\n\nLeakhena Seang (11:23 A.M.)\nI have plenty to go around. We'll be creating mosaic designs using bits of sea glass I collected on my vacation last summer. They are pieces of brown, green, and blue bottles that have washed up on the beach. The sand has smoothed all the sharp edges, so they're perfectly safe for everyone to use.\n\nCarol Barger (11:30 A.M.)\nSounds good. See you tomorrow at breakfast.", "qs": [{"n": 149, "q": "What most likely is Ms. Seang's job?", "opts": ["Glassmaker", "Art instructor", "Beach lifeguard", "Program administrator"], "ans": 1, "note": "쌤 씨의 직업 추론: 바거 씨가 내일 열리는 모자이크 워크숍에 참가자 15명이 등록했다고 알려주는 것으로 보아 쌤 씨는 미술 강사임을 알 수 있다. 정답 (B)."}, {"n": 150, "q": "At 11:23 A.M., what does Ms. Seang imply when she writes, \"I have plenty to go around\"?", "opts": ["She intends to create an extra-large mosaic.", "She has been collecting sea glass for many years.", "She can share her sea glass with all the workshop participants.", "She does not think she will use much of her sea glass."], "ans": 2, "note": "쌤 씨가 '모두에게 나눠줄 만큼 충분히 있어요'라고 쓴 의도: 지난 여름휴가 때 모아둔 바다 유리 조각이 워크숍 참가자 전원에게 나눠줄 수 있을 만큼 충분하다는 의도. 정답 (C)."}]}, {"title": "Questions 151-152 refer to the following e-mail.", "passage": "*E-mail*\nTo: Sales Team\nFrom: Laura Correa\nDate: 5 October\nSubject: Updates\n\nDear Team,\n\nAs announced in the Brighter Sails September newsletter, our performance has been consistently strong this year. This is an accomplishment we can all be proud of. Please take a moment to congratulate each other. We will continue to dream up new and exciting plans for the future!\n\nIn other news, Jasen Norton will transfer to our Kingston headquarters next month. We are sad to lose Mr. Norton, but we gratefully acknowledge his excellent work and wish him continued success in his new role.\n\nThere will be a farewell luncheon for Mr. Norton on 28 October at 1:00 P.M. in the second-floor conference room. Bring your good cheer and perhaps a story to share. The company will supply lunch, a cake, and decorations. Let me know by 12 October whether you will be able to attend.\n\nSincerely,\n\nLaura Correa, Sales Manager\nBrighter Sails Ltd.", "qs": [{"n": 151, "q": "What is mentioned about Mr. Norton?", "opts": ["He will be attending a sales conference.", "He sent Ms. Correa an office supply request.", "He wrote an article in the September newsletter.", "He will be moving to another company location."], "ans": 3, "note": "노턴 씨에 대해 언급된 것: 두 번째 단락 첫 문장에서 제이슨 노턴 씨가 다음 달 킹스턴 본사로 전근할 예정이라고 했으므로 회사의 다른 지점으로 옮길 예정이다가 정답."}, {"n": 152, "q": "What does Ms. Correa ask members of the sales team to do?", "opts": ["Send her stories for a newsletter", "Give her names of potential new hires", "Inform her of plans to attend an event", "Help her decorate the office"], "ans": 2, "note": "코레아 씨가 영업팀원들에게 요청하는 것: 마지막 단락 마지막 문장에서 10월 12일까지 참석 가능 여부를 알려달라고 요청하므로 행사 참석 계획을 알리기가 정답."}]}, {"title": "Questions 153-154 refer to the following article.", "passage": "Refurbished Theater Gives Town a Boost\n\nBEACHVILLE (February 24)—Beachville residents and tourists have a good reason to celebrate. The 40-year-old Crown Coastal Theater is scheduled to reopen in June. Many were saddened when the former theater owners decided to close the venue over a year ago, citing the cost of needed renovations. Fortunately, the theater has new owners who have spent the last year updating the interior and the projection system.\n\nChristine Lafferty said that she and her childhood friend Morgan Flanagan spent plenty of time at the theater while growing up. \"Going to the movies is the thing to do on a rainy day in a seaside town. We were sorry to see it close.\" The friends, who also own the popular Blue Bay Bistro, decided to buy the theater and make the necessary repairs to keep it a thriving business. For more information about the theater and its upcoming events, visit www.crowncoastaltheater.com.", "qs": [{"n": 153, "q": "What is the purpose of the article?", "opts": ["To report on beach conditions", "To announce a business reopening", "To promote a movie premiere", "To advertise a new restaurant"], "ans": 1, "note": "기사의 목적: 첫 단락 두 번째 문장에서 40년 된 크라운 코스탈 극장이 6월에 다시 개관 예정이라고 하므로 영업 재개를 알리려고가 정답."}, {"n": 154, "q": "Who is Ms. Flanagan?", "opts": ["A town council member", "An event coordinator", "Ms. Lafferty's business partner", "The writer of the article"], "ans": 2, "note": "플래너건 씨는 누구인가: 두 번째 단락 첫 문장에서 크리스틴 래퍼티가 어린 시절 친구인 모건 플래너건과 자라면서 극장에서 많은 시간을 보냈다고 하므로 래퍼티 씨의 동업자가 정답."}]}, {"title": "Questions 155-157 refer to the following e-mail.", "passage": "*E-mail*\nTo: Randi Longfellow <rlongfellow@sapphiremail.com.au>\nFrom: Deon Welman <deonwelman@skyviewscopes.com.au>\nDate: 27 March\nSubject: Makatasi model METX-33948\n\nDear Ms. Longfellow,\n\nThank you for ordering the Makatasi ETX-Triple Refracting Telescope, model METX-33948. Unfortunately, the item you requested is on back order. — [1] —. If you would prefer not to wait, we have a similar telescope made by another manufacturer, Belter Telescopes. Like the Makatasi model you ordered, the Belter BTR-1483 has a 120 mm aperture and a retractable lens hood. — [2] —. In addition, all Belter telescopes include a padded carrying case. The Belter BTR-1483 costs $200 less than the Makatasi METX-33948.\n\nIf you wish to revise your order, simply reply to this e-mail within 48 hours or go to our Web site to chat with a representative at http://www.skyviewscopes.com.au. We will then change your order, refund $200 to your credit card, and ship your new telescope overnight at no extra charge. — [3] —. Otherwise, we will notify you when the Makatasi model METX-33948 is back in stock and provide delivery information at that point. — [4] —.\n\nBest regards,\n\nDeon Welman\nSales Representative, Skyview Scopes", "qs": [{"n": 155, "q": "What is the purpose of the e-mail?", "opts": ["To request payment", "To provide operating instructions", "To advertise a new product", "To offer a substitute item"], "ans": 3, "note": "이메일의 목적은? 정답 (D) 대체 제품을 제안하려고. 고객이 요청한 제품은 현재 주문이 밀려 있어(on back order) 다른 제조업체가 만든 유사한 망원경을 대신 제안하는 이메일이다."}, {"n": 156, "q": "What is mentioned about the Belter BTR-1483 telescope?", "opts": ["It can only be ordered online.", "It will ship directly from the manufacturer.", "It includes a protective case.", "It is the most expensive telescope of its type."], "ans": 2, "note": "벨터 BTR-1483 망원경에 대해 언급된 것은? 정답 (C) 보호용 케이스가 들어 있다. 모든 벨터 망원경에는 패딩 처리된 휴대용 케이스가 포함된다(a padded carrying case)고 했으므로 케이스가 제공됨을 알 수 있다. (a padded carrying case → a protective case)"}, {"n": 157, "q": "In which of the positions marked [1], [2], [3], and [4] does the following sentence best belong? \"You can see a full list of specifications on our Web site.\"", "opts": ["[1]", "[2]", "[3]", "[4]"], "ans": 1, "note": "문장 삽입: '저희 웹사이트에서 전체 사양 목록을 확인하실 수 있습니다.'가 들어갈 위치는? 정답 (B) [2]. 앞에 제품의 일부 사양(120mm 조리개와 접이식 렌즈 후드)을 소개하는 문장 뒤인 [2]에 들어가는 것이 자연스럽다."}]}, {"title": "Questions 158-160 refer to the following e-mail.", "passage": "To: Sun-Hi Myo <shmyo@sunmail.co.nz>\nFrom: Jan Delpit <jdelpit@hamerkoptech.co.nz>\nDate: 8 March\nSubject: RE: Inquiry about job opening\n\nHello,\n\nThank you for your e-mail. I am currently on holiday and will return to the office on 15 March. I will respond to your message as soon as possible after I return.\n\nIf you require general assistance during my absence or have questions about the open position in our sales department, please contact my assistant Sita Viswan at 04 555 0193 or sviswan@hamerkoptech.co.nz. For questions about specific Hamerkoptech software products, contact the customer service department at customerservice@hamerkoptech.co.nz.\n\nAdditionally, I am happy to announce that our new graphic design software program will be released on 2 April. You can read more about the program at Hamerkoptech's newly redesigned Web site, www.hamerkoptech.co.nz. There, you may also sign up to receive our weekly newsletter by following the instructions on the home page.\n\nSincerely,\n\nJan Delpit", "qs": [{"n": 158, "q": "What is one purpose of the e-mail?", "opts": ["To explain how to use a software program", "To request Ms. Myo's assistance with a project", "To introduce a new staff member", "To indicate that Mr. Delpit is out of the office"], "ans": 1, "note": "이메일의 목적: 델핏 씨가 휴가 중으로 사무실에 없음을 알리려는 것. 첫 단락에서 3월 15일에 복귀 예정이며 복귀하는 대로 답하겠다고 했으므로 (D)가 정답."}, {"n": 159, "q": "What will happen on April 2 ?", "opts": ["A job opening will be filled.", "A product will be launched.", "A client meeting will take place.", "A Web site redesign will begin."], "ans": 2, "note": "4월 2일에 일어날 일: 제품이 출시된다. 세 번째 단락에서 새 그래픽 디자인 소프트웨어 프로그램이 4월 2일에 출시될 예정이라고 했으므로 (B)가 정답."}, {"n": 160, "q": "How can people subscribe to a newsletter?", "opts": ["By calling Ms. Viswan", "By replying to Mr. Delpit's e-mail", "By visiting Hamerkoptech's Web site", "By contacting the customer service department"], "ans": 2, "note": "소식지를 구독하는 방법: 하머콥테크의 웹사이트를 방문함으로써. 새로 개편된 웹사이트에서 홈페이지 안내에 따라 주간 소식지 수령을 신청할 수 있다고 했으므로 (C)가 정답."}]}, {"title": "Questions 161-163 refer to the following article.", "passage": "Vimalo Brands Enters a New Era\nBy Yvette Maurer\n\nVANCOUVER (2 August)—Vimalo Brands, the large consumer goods company that markets popular nutritional-support and personal-care products, including Powerburst breakfast drinks and Honeysoft soaps and lotions, will soon offer something new for its customers: frozen foods. \"Our new Nutridinna line is not just about convenience,\" CEO Danitza Martens said during a press conference earlier today. \"Frozen foods are not a new concept, but our method of flash-freezing fresh produce and meats ensures that our products retain their texture and flavour as well as their healthy vitamins and minerals. Now our customers can enjoy the convenience of frozen food without sacrificing quality.\"\n\nVimalo Brands has partnered with Vancouver-area farms to obtain produce and meat for the Nutridinna line. \"By keeping our operations local, we avoid shipping delays and can flash-freeze freshly harvested vegetables at their peak of ripeness,\" Martens said. \"Our customers benefit further, since our products can be kept in the freezer for up to six months.\" Nutridinna foods will be available in supermarkets beginning in November. Frozen fish and other seafood will be added early next year.", "qs": [{"n": 161, "q": "What is one purpose of the article?", "opts": ["To discuss a cooking technique", "To report on a corporate merger", "To announce a new product line", "To introduce a recently hired executive"], "ans": 2, "note": "기사의 목적 중 하나는? 첫 단락 첫 문장에서 비말로 브랜즈가 곧 고객들에게 냉동식품 신제품을 선보일 예정이라고 했으므로 신제품 라인 발표가 목적이다. (C)"}, {"n": 162, "q": "The word \"just\" in paragraph 1, line 8, is closest in meaning to", "opts": ["recently", "exactly", "slightly", "only"], "ans": 3, "note": "첫 단락 8행의 'just'와 의미가 가장 가까운 것은? 새 제품 라인이 '단지' 편리한 것뿐만 아니라는 뜻으로 쓰였으므로 '단지, 오로지'를 뜻하는 (D) only가 정답이다."}, {"n": 163, "q": "What does Ms. Martens suggest about flash-frozen food?", "opts": ["It is less expensive than fresh food.", "It is as nutritious as fresh food.", "It is as easy to ship as fresh food.", "It is less flavorful than fresh food."], "ans": 1, "note": "마르텐스 씨가 급속 냉동식품에 대해 암시하는 것은? 신선한 농산물과 육류를 급속 냉동시키면 제품이 식감과 맛뿐 아니라 건강에 유익한 비타민과 미네랄을 유지하도록 보장한다고 했으므로, 냉동 식품도 신선 식품 못지않게 영양이 보장된다는 (B)가 정답이다."}]}, {"title": "Questions 164-167 refer to the following advertisement.", "passage": "Are you ready to work hard as part of a team of like-minded individuals? Are you willing to put your education, your experience, and your imagination to great use? If so, then we have the job for you. Karning Creative Designs is expanding, and with our success comes your opportunity.\nKarning Creative Designs began ten years ago as a two-person operation set up in the home of our current CEO and founder Shirin Navani. Now located in a beautiful loft in downtown Hollinson, our firm currently employs 25 full-time staff members. At Karning, we design paper-based brochures, catalogs, ads, and posters for our clients. We are currently seeking qualified designers and artists who will shine in a fast-paced, collaborative environment.\nThe ideal candidate\n• Holds a degree in design, advertising, or graphic art—although several years of direct experience may substitute for a degree\n• Demonstrates a strong ability to work closely with colleagues\n• Maintains a critical eye for detail and precision\n• Consistently meets deadlines and can flourish under pressure\nGraphic design or related experience is a plus but not strictly necessary.\nIf you are ready to join our team, we want to meet you! Contact Salvador Tomassin at 608-555-0144 for further details. All applications must be received by March 31.", "qs": [{"n": 164, "q": "According to the advertisement, who most likely is Ms. Navani?", "opts": ["A Karning Creative Designs client", "A business owner", "A photographer", "A real estate agent"], "ans": 2, "note": "광고에 따르면 나바니 씨는 누구인 것 같은가? 두 번째 단락 첫 문장에서 카닝 크리에이티브 디자인즈는 현 CEO이자 창립자인 시린 나바니의 집에서 설립된 2인 기업으로 10년 전 시작했다고 했으므로, 나바니 씨는 소유주임을 알 수 있다. (B)"}, {"n": 165, "q": "What is indicated about Karning Creative Designs?", "opts": ["Its primary focus is Web design.", "It initially employed two people.", "It was founded by Mr. Tomassin.", "Its staff are permitted to work from home."], "ans": 1, "note": "카닝 크리에이티브 디자인즈에 대해 명시된 것: 창립 당시 직원이 2명이었다(2인 기업으로 시작). 지문의 'as a two-person operation'이 정답의 'initially employed two people'로 패러프레이징."}, {"n": 166, "q": "What is required of job applicants?", "opts": ["Skill in working with others", "Previous design experience", "A willingness to work on weekends", "An ability to use certain software applications"], "ans": 0, "note": "취업 지원자에게 요구되는 것: 다른 사람들과 밀접하게 협업할 수 있는 강한 능력. 'ability to work closely with colleagues'가 정답의 'skill in working with others'."}, {"n": 167, "q": "What will happen on March 31?", "opts": ["A project will begin.", "A deadline will occur.", "A graphic designer will relocate.", "An application form will be made available."], "ans": 1, "note": "3월 31일에 일어날 일: 마감일이 된다. 모든 지원서는 3월 31일까지 접수되어야 한다고 명시(applications must be received by March 31)되어 입사 지원 마감일임을 알 수 있음."}]}, {"title": "Questions 168-171 refer to the following article.", "passage": "NEW HAVEN (June 1)—Marco's Italian Restaurant on Frontage Road will be reopening in late June. It closed three months ago after a water leak caused extensive damage to the kitchen. A significant amount of work needed to be done in the kitchen and dining areas. — [1] —. The restaurant will accommodate larger parties when it reopens.\n\nDuring the past three months, many of the restaurant's employees were able to work at Marco's Italian Market, which is located on the opposite side of the street. — [2] —. \"The leak happened right before the market's busy season started,\" said Tom Marco, who owns both businesses. \"We needed to add staff there temporarily, and I was happy to keep my restaurant crew employed.\" Most of those employees have now returned to work in the restaurant. — [3] —.\n\nMr. Marco has planned a grand reopening for June 25. Guests will enjoy live music and a new tasting menu. — [4] —. Reservations are required for the day of the celebration and can be made by calling 203-555-0124. \"We are excited to be able to prepare our traditional dishes and welcome the community back again,\" stated Mr. Marco.", "qs": [{"n": 168, "q": "What does the article mention about Marco's Italian Restaurant?", "opts": ["It is the oldest restaurant in New Haven.", "It is looking for a chef who can cook traditional dishes.", "It needed major renovations.", "It opened in a new location."], "ans": 2, "note": "기사에서 마르코즈 이탈리안 레스토랑에 대해 언급한 것: 대대적인 보수 공사가 필요했다. 3개월 전 누수로 주방에 막대한 피해가 발생해 문을 닫았고 주방·식사 공간에 상당한 작업이 필요했음. 'a significant amount of work'가 정답의 'major renovations'."}, {"n": 169, "q": "What is indicated about Marco's Italian Market?", "opts": ["It supplies ingredients to Marco's Italian Restaurant.", "It occasionally hires temporary workers.", "It is scheduled to close in three months.", "It is located next door to Marco's Italian Restaurant."], "ans": 1, "note": "마르코즈 이탈리안 마켓에 대해 명시된 것: 가끔 임시 직원을 고용한다. 마켓 소유주 톰 마르코즈가 '누수는 시장 성수기 직전에 발생했다'며 그곳에 일시적으로 직원을 늘릴 필요가 있었다고 말함."}, {"n": 170, "q": "What will happen during the event on June 25 ?", "opts": ["The restaurant will reduce its menu prices.", "The restaurant will offer special menu items.", "Mr. Marco will celebrate his retirement.", "The New Haven business community will honor Mr. Marco."], "ans": 3, "note": "6월 25일 행사 중에 일어날 일은? 정답은 (B) 식당이 특별 메뉴를 제공할 것이다. 마르코 씨가 6월 25일 성대한 재개점을 계획 중이며 손님들이 라이브 음악과 새로운 시식 메뉴를 즐길 것이라고 했으므로 특별 메뉴를 선보일 예정이다."}, {"n": 171, "q": "In which of the positions marked [1], [2], [3], and [4] does the following sentence best belong? \"During repairs, some additional dining space was added.\"", "opts": ["[1]", "[2]", "[3]", "[4]"], "ans": 0, "note": "문장 삽입: '보수 공사 중에 추가적인 식사 공간이 더해졌다'가 들어갈 위치는 (A) [1]. 재개점하면 더 큰 단체 손님을 수용할 수 있다는 내용 앞 [1]에 들어가는 것이 자연스럽다."}]}, {"title": "Questions 172-175 refer to the following online chat discussion.", "passage": "Marlys Barry (10:17 A.M.)\nThis is Ms. Barry from the data analysis department. I have included my colleague, Ms. Choi. We're contacting you about your data request for the e-mail addresses of all account holders, sorted by age.\n\nAlexander Kubelski (10:17 A.M.)\nYes, how soon can you complete the request?\n\nMarlys Barry (10:18 A.M.)\nI have a question for you first. Do you really need the e-mail addresses of all account holders? That would be a huge file. Or do you need the e-mail addresses of account holders only within a certain age-group?\n\nAlexander Kubelski (10:19 A.M.)\nI see what you mean. I want to e-mail account holders aged 55 to 65 to invite them to meet with a retirement planning expert. Do I have to submit a new project request form?\n\nBora Choi (10:21 A.M.)\nThat's not necessary, Mr. Kubelski. We can update your current request form for you. You do not want to lose your place in the queue.\n\nAlexander Kubelski (10:21 A.M.)\nGreat, thank you! Is it possible for you to get me that list right away?\n\nMarlys Barry (10:22 A.M.)\nThere are several projects ahead of yours.\n\nAlexander Kubelski (10:23 A.M.)\nI was hoping to send out the e-mail invitations tomorrow.\n\nMarlys Barry (10:24 A.M.)\nWe will get to it as soon as we can.", "qs": [{"n": 172, "q": "Why did Ms. Barry begin an online chat with Mr. Kubelski?", "opts": ["To refer him to a different department", "To decline an invitation", "To issue an apology", "To ask for clarification about a request"], "ans": 3, "note": "배리 씨가 쿠벨스키 씨와 온라인 채팅을 시작한 이유는? 정답은 (D) 요청 건에 대한 설명을 요구하기 위해서. 모든 계정 보유자의 이메일 주소를 연령별로 정리한 데이터 요청과 관련해 연락했으므로 세부 사항을 확인하려는 것이다."}, {"n": 173, "q": "Who will receive an e-mail from Mr. Kubelski?", "opts": ["Account holders in one age-group", "Data analysis team members", "Financial planners", "All Mr. Kubelski's clients"], "ans": 0, "note": "쿠벨스키 씨로부터 누가 이메일을 받게 될 것인가? 정답은 (A) 한 연령대에 속한 계정 보유자들. 55세에서 65세 사이의 계정 보유자들에게 은퇴 설계 전문가와의 만남에 초대하는 이메일을 보내려 한다."}, {"n": 174, "q": "What does Ms. Choi offer to do?", "opts": ["Write an e-mail", "Make a change to a form", "Open an account", "Revise a policy"], "ans": 1, "note": "세부 사항. 최 씨는 무엇을 하겠다고 제안하는가? 10시 21분에 최 씨가 현재 요청서를 대신 수정해 줄 수 있다(We can update your current request form for you)고 제안하므로 (B) 양식 수정이 정답."}, {"n": 175, "q": "At 10:22 A.M., what does Ms. Barry most likely mean when she writes, \"There are several projects ahead of yours\"?", "opts": ["Ms. Barry will move Mr. Kubelski's request to the end of the queue.", "Ms. Barry will not be able to send out the invitations for Mr. Kubelski.", "Mr. Kubelski's request will not be the first job Ms. Barry completes.", "Mr. Kubelski will need to assist with other projects first."], "ans": 2, "note": "의도 파악. 배리 씨가 '요청하신 건보다 먼저 해야 할 프로젝트가 몇 개 있어요'라고 쓴 의도는? 쿠벨스키 씨가 목록을 바로 줄 수 있는지 묻자 먼저 할 프로젝트가 있다고 답한 것으로, 쿠벨스키 씨의 요청은 배리 씨가 먼저 완료할 작업이 아니라는 (C)가 정답."}]}, {"title": "Questions 176-180 refer to the following article and e-mail.", "passage": "Tips for designing a Web site for a food-truck business\n\nOwners of food trucks move from place to place, within and between cities, as they carry out their business, so they often rely on word of mouth or social media to attract customers. As a result, they may not build a Web site of their own. But in fact, by the very nature of their business, it is crucial that food truck owners have a fixed place for the public to learn about them, order from them, contact them, etc. Furthermore, market research shows that a Web site can help build a loyal customer base. So, here are some tips for developing a great Web site for your food truck.\n\nThe Home page should have bold graphics with your food truck's name. The text must prominently display key information, such as your truck's locations and operating hours. Online forms with fields to fill out, such as reservation requests for special events or services, give new visitors too much visual information. They are better incorporated as links or pop-up windows.\n\nThe Food Menu page needs attractive, high-definition images along with vivid and precise text that describes each menu item in detail. Remember that your photos should be big enough to look appealing on larger computer monitors.\n\nThe About Us page should include some text explaining your food truck's theme and concept, and some biographical data detailing your background in the food industry.\n\nThe News page can include text informing visitors about seasonal food items and upcoming promotions or special events such as food festivals.\n\nTo: Doug Abruzzo <dabruzzo@dzacreative.com>\nFrom: Ed Vale <evale@saffronmail.com>\nDate: March 29\nSubject: Feedback\n\nDear Mr. Abruzzo,\n\nThank you again for creating the prototype Web site for my food-truck business. I just wanted to reiterate that it has gotten positive feedback from customers who have tested it. I am so glad we followed the advice in that article you sent me about Web site design for food trucks!\n\nAs we discussed in our phone call yesterday, we will move forward with the prototype Web site and launch it as the official site on April 5. However, I still do not see the information I sent about our new promotion that will begin in mid-April, a free dessert with any sandwich purchase. Please be sure to add this important information before we launch the site.\n\nRegards,\n\nEd", "qs": [{"n": 176, "q": "According to the article, what is one way that food truck owners traditionally attract customers?", "opts": ["By word of mouth", "From highway billboards", "Through newspaper advertisements", "From signs at food festivals"], "ans": 0, "note": "세부 사항. 기사에 따르면 푸드트럭 소유주들이 전통적으로 고객을 유치하는 한 가지 방법은? 도시 여러 곳으로 옮겨 다니며 입소문이나 소셜 미디어에 의존한다고 하므로 (A) 입소문이 정답."}, {"n": 177, "q": "According to the article, what information does not need to appear on the Home page?", "opts": ["Truck locations", "Hours of operation", "Company name", "Seasonal food items"], "ans": 3, "note": "메인 페이지에 게시될 필요가 없는 정보를 묻는 문제. 두 번째 단락에서 메인(Home) 페이지에는 트럭 이름과 위치·운영 시간 같은 핵심 정보가 표시돼야 한다고 했고, 계절 음식 메뉴는 소식(News) 페이지에 들어갈 정보이므로 (D) 계절 음식 메뉴가 정답."}, {"n": 178, "q": "In what field does Mr. Abruzzo most likely work?", "opts": ["Market research", "Catering", "Web design", "Package delivery"], "ans": 2, "note": "아브루쪼 씨가 어떤 분야에서 일할지 묻는 문제. 이메일 첫 문장에서 웹사이트 견본(prototype Web site) 제작에 감사한다고 한 것으로 보아 웹디자인 일을 함을 알 수 있어 (C) 웹디자인이 정답."}, {"n": 179, "q": "In which section of the Web site will information most likely be added?", "opts": ["The Home page", "The Food Menu page", "The About Us page", "The News page"], "ans": 3, "note": "정보가 웹사이트의 어느 섹션에 추가될지 묻는 문제. 무료 디저트 판촉 등 판촉 행사·푸드 페스티벌 같은 특별 행사 정보는 소식(News) 페이지에 들어가야 하므로 (D) 소식 페이지가 정답."}, {"n": 180, "q": "According to the e-mail, when will the Web site launch?", "opts": ["On March 28", "On March 29", "On April 5", "On April 15"], "ans": 3, "note": "웹사이트가 언제 개시될 예정인지 묻는 문제. 4월 5일에 견본을 공식 웹사이트로 개시할 예정(launch it as the official site on April 5)이라 했으므로 (C) 4월 5일이 정답."}]}, {"title": "Questions 181-185 refer to the following e-mail and press release.", "passage": "*E-mail*\nTo: Manny Green <mgreen@rhba.com>\nFrom: John LaRose <jlarose@rilamore.edu>\nDate: May 18\nSubject: Drilling notice\n\nDear Mr. Green:\n\nAs a courtesy, I am writing to you at the Red Hills Business Association, asking you to help me get the word out to your membership. It was announced in last month's Daily Gazette that Rilamore University is moving forward with its Net Zero Initiative. Within three years, we expect to have geothermal wells installed and operational for the heating and cooling of our entire campus. Limiting the institution's reliance on fossil fuels has long been a goal, and the new system is a significant step toward achieving that goal.\n\nOver the next month, we will conduct test drilling in several campus locations. If all goes according to schedule, the crew will be drilling adjacent to the Red Hills Business District and Oak Street Apartments starting Wednesday, June 5. We want to tell business owners and residents near the campus to expect a higher-than-usual noise level during the two weeks we estimate it will take to complete the work. The work hours for the drilling crew are 10 A.M. to 3 P.M. each day, Monday through Friday.\n\nWe apologize in advance for the inconvenience this may cause to our neighbors. Any questions or concerns should be directed to me at 813-555-0123.\n\nJohn LaRose\nCommunity Liaison, Rilamore University Office of Communications\n\nFOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE\n\nContact: Manny Green, mgreen@rhba.com\n\nRED HILLS (May 25)—The Red Hills Business Association is shifting the dates of its much-anticipated Lunch Hour Concert Series. Normally presented each Thursday in June, the four free concerts will instead take place each Thursday in July. The lineup of artists remains unchanged—the Jaystone Jazz Trio will open the series on July 4, followed on successive Thursdays by Joss and the Jaybirds, Ray Starform, and the Barklay Bass Quintet.\n\nAs usual, all three blocks of Oak Street will be closed to traffic, restaurants will serve lunch at outdoor tables, and local arts-and-crafts vendors will display their work on the lawn of the Cultural Center. It is a beautiful celebration in the heart of a popular Red Hills neighborhood. We hope to see you there!", "qs": [{"n": 181, "q": "What is indicated about the Net Zero Initiative?", "opts": ["It is being funded by the Red Hills Business Association.", "It was inspired by similar initiatives in other cities.", "It will use geothermal energy to power a city.", "It will change the way an institution heats its buildings."], "ans": 3, "note": "넷 제로 이니셔티브에 대해 명시된 것: 이메일 첫 단락에서 릴라모어 대학교가 넷 제로 이니셔티브를 진행하며 3년 내 캠퍼스 전체 냉난방을 위해 지열 우물을 설치·운영해 화석 연료 의존을 줄일 것이라 했으므로, 기관의 건물을 난방하는 방식을 바꿀 것이다(D)가 정답."}, {"n": 182, "q": "In the e-mail, the word \"conduct\" in paragraph 2, line 1, is closest in meaning to", "opts": ["behave", "accompany", "transmit", "carry out"], "ans": 3, "note": "이메일 두 번째 단락 1행의 'conduct'와 의미가 가장 가까운 것: '시추 테스트를 수행할 것'이라는 뜻으로 쓰였으므로 '수행하다, 실행하다'를 뜻하는 carry out(D)이 정답."}, {"n": 183, "q": "What can be concluded about the Red Hills Business District?", "opts": ["It is located near a university campus.", "It hosts an arts festival every July.", "It includes the Oak Street Apartments.", "It is home to the offices of the Daily Gazette."], "ans": 0, "note": "레드 힐스 비즈니스 지구에 대해 결론지을 수 있는 것: 캠퍼스 내 여러 위치에서 시추 테스트를 수행하며 작업팀이 6월 5일부터 레드 힐스 비즈니스 지구와 오크 가 아파트 인근에서 시추한다고 했으므로 대학 캠퍼스 근처에 있음(A)이 정답."}, {"n": 184, "q": "Why most likely did the Red Hills Business Association change the dates of its concert series?", "opts": ["To take advantage of a new power source", "To accommodate students' schedules", "To avoid noise from nearby construction", "To prevent a conflict with a similar event"], "ans": 2, "note": "레드 힐스 비즈니스 협회가 콘서트 시리즈 날짜를 변경한 이유: 작업팀이 6월 5일부터 레드 힐스 비즈니스 지구와 오크 가 아파트 인근에서 시추하게 되어 캠퍼스 주변 근처 공사 소음을 피하기 위해서(C)가 정답."}, {"n": 185, "q": "What is mentioned in the press release about the Cultural Center?", "opts": ["It will provide lunch for musicians.", "It will have artwork for sale on its property.", "It will offer arts-and-crafts workshops.", "It will provide the stage for performers."], "ans": 1, "note": "문화 센터에 대해 보도 자료에 언급된 것은? 보도 자료 두 번째 단락 첫 문장에서 지역 미술상 및 공예상인들은 문화센터 잔디밭에 작품을 전시할 예정이라 했으므로 (B) 건물 부지에 판매용 미술품을 놓을 것이다가 정답. (arts-and-crafts vendors will display their work → artwork for sale)"}]}, {"title": "Questions 186-190 refer to the following advertisement, form, and review.", "passage": "Lawal Home Service: Serving Southern California for over 40 years\n\nLawal Home Service provides roofing and solar solutions for Southern California residents in Inglewood and the surrounding areas. In addition to roof replacement, we offer a wide array of services, from attic insulation and gutter restoration to fixing leaks and installing solar panels.\n\nLawal Home Service prides itself on transparent communication and attention to detail. Our project supervisors are always on-site to answer client questions, provide updates, and ensure a safe and clean worksite. To request a free roofing diagnosis, visit www.lawalhomeservice.com or call our booking agent at 310-555-0108.\n\nLawal Home Service Contact Form\n\nTrust the experts at Lawal Home Service to diagnose your roofing needs promptly and professionally. Please take a few minutes to complete the form with as much detail as possible. Remember, all roofs installed by Lawal have a 25-year warranty.\n\nName: Drew Gerson\nDate: December 12\nE-mail: dgerson95@onyxmail.com\nPhone: 310-555-0192\nAddress: 820 North Acacia Street, Inglewood, CA 90301\nHow may we help you?: During last week's windstorm, several roof shingles were torn loose and need replacing. I am considering replacing the entire roof as it is over 30 years old, and water has begun to drip through the section over the patio. I would appreciate talking to someone who could tell me my options and provide an estimate.\nNeighborhood Reviews: Lawal Home Service\n\n★★★★★\n\n\"I was very pleased with the thoroughness of their work.\"\n\nI left a description of my problem with Lawal Home Service, and one of the company's estimators came to inspect my roof the very next day. After I decided to replace the roof, the Lawal Home Service crew was able to get to work the following week. Diana Perez was on-site for the whole job as promised and answered all my questions. Work was started on December 19, and it was finished on December 20. Once the roofing was finished, the crew did a great job cleaning up. They used two magnetic devices resembling lawnmowers and swept over my entire lawn to find any dropped roofing nails. I had never seen anything like that! I was very pleased with the thoroughness of their work.\n\n— Drew Gerson, Inglewood, CA", "qs": [{"n": 186, "q": "According to the advertisement, what is one type of work performed by Lawal Home Service?", "opts": ["Planting trees", "Repairing gutters", "Building home additions", "Replacing heating systems"], "ans": 1, "note": "광고에 따르면 로얼 홈 서비스가 수행하는 작업 종류 중 하나는? 광고 첫 단락에서 다락방 단열, 홈통 복구 등 다양한 서비스를 제공한다고 했으므로 (B) 홈통 수리가 정답."}, {"n": 187, "q": "What does Mr. Gerson indicate on the form about his roof?", "opts": ["It has developed a leak.", "It was recently replaced.", "It was not expensive to install.", "It is under warranty for 30 years."], "ans": 2, "note": "거슨 씨가 양식에서 자신의 지붕에 대해 명시한 것은? 물이 떨어지기 시작해 전체 지붕 교체를 고민 중이라고 했으므로 (A) 누수가 발생했다가 정답."}, {"n": 188, "q": "When did Lawal Home Service inspect Mr. Gerson's roof?", "opts": ["On December 12", "On December 13", "On December 19", "On December 20"], "ans": 1, "note": "로얼 홈 서비스는 언제 거슨 씨의 지붕을 점검했는가? 거슨 씨가 12월 12일 양식을 작성했고 그 다음 날 견적 담당자가 점검하러 왔으므로 (B) 12월 13일이 정답."}, {"n": 189, "q": "Who most likely is Ms. Perez?", "opts": ["A project supervisor", "A roofing estimator", "An interior decorator", "A booking agent"], "ans": 0, "note": "페레즈 씨는 누구인 것 같은가? 다이애나 페레즈가 작업 내내 현장에 있으며 프로젝트 감독관은 항상 현장에 있다고 했으므로 (A) 프로젝트 감독관이 정답."}, {"n": 190, "q": "According to the review, what surprised Mr. Gerson about the crew from Lawal Home Service?", "opts": ["The price they charged", "The warranty they offered", "The quality of their materials", "The tools they used for a job"], "ans": 3, "note": "거슨 씨는 로얼 홈 서비스 작업팀의 어떤 점에 놀랐는가? 잔디 깎는 기계처럼 생긴 자기 장치로 지붕 못을 찾아냈다고 감탄했으므로 (D) 그들이 작업에 사용한 도구가 정답."}]}, {"title": "Questions 191-195 refer to the following e-mails and form.", "passage": "To: Omar Balaji <obalaji@darbourycompany.com>\nFrom: Juanita Pereira <jpereira@bunbunbooks.com>\nDate: May 10\nSubject: Notebook inquiry\n\nDear Mr. Balaji,\n\nWe are expanding our office supply section at Bun Bun Books and would like to offer a selection of blank notebooks with lined pages. We would like your help creating the following cover designs.\n\nCover Design Name | Central Image | Background Color\nGreat Thoughts | Lightbulb, lightning bolt, and star icons | Blue\nWorld Suitcase | Suitcase with country name travel stickers | Black\nLavender Bouquet | Large bunch of lavender on tall, pale green stems | Yellow\nSail Away | Sun setting in the sky above a sailboat on a lake | White\n\nWe need to have notebooks in stock in time for our annual sale starting August 1. After approving the sample covers, when would we need to place our order?\n\nThank you,\nJuanita Pereira\nTo: Juanita Pereira <jpereira@bunbunbooks.com>\nFrom: Omar Balaji <obalaji@darbourycompany.com>\nDate: May 25\nSubject: Re: Notebook inquiry\n\nHello, Ms. Pereira,\n\nI have shipped some sample notebook covers for your inspection. Unfortunately, I was not able to include one of the designs for your approval because it needed a late-stage change to the background color. The sticker art did not show up well against the original black background. We are testing a light-beige color, and I will send the updated sample cover to you after it has been approved internally.\n\nI should have the last sample to you by the end of this week. As long as you send your approval of all covers by June 11, we will be able to ship your entire order of bound notebooks before July 20. You will have everything before your sale that begins on August 1. Please contact me if you have any questions.\n\nBest regards,\nOmar Balaji, Darboury Company\nDarboury Company\nOrder Form\n\nCustomer: Bun Bun Books\nShip by: July 15\nShipping method: Standard\nRequested delivery date: July 20\n\nItem code | Product Description | Cover Design | Amount\nN3-GT | Standard-size spiral notebook | Great Thoughts | 200\nN3-WS | Standard-size spiral notebook | World Suitcase | 200\nH3-LB | Small hardbound journal notebook | Lavender Bouquet | 150\nH3-SA | Small hardbound journal notebook | Sail Away | 150\nD1 | Large metal display rack (holds standard-size spiral notebooks) | — | 1", "qs": [{"n": 191, "q": "What is one service that Darboury Company most likely provides?", "opts": ["Travel booking", "Textbook publishing", "Flower delivery", "Graphic design"], "ans": 3, "note": "번역: 다버리 컴퍼니에서 제공할 가능성이 높은 서비스는? (D) 그래픽 디자인. 해설: 첫 이메일 수신인이 다버리 컴퍼니 이메일 주소이고, 표지 디자인 제작 도움을 요청한 것으로 보아 그래픽 디자인 서비스를 제공하는 회사임을 유추할 수 있다."}, {"n": 192, "q": "What sample was delayed?", "opts": ["Great Thoughts", "World Suitcase", "Lavender Bouquet", "Sail Away"], "ans": 1, "note": "번역: 어떤 샘플이 지연되었는가? (B) 세계 여행 가방. 해설: 두 번째 이메일에서 배경 색상에 막판 수정이 필요해 승인이 필요한 디자인을 포함시키지 못했다고 했고, 세계 여행 가방의 배경 색상이 검정으로 나와 있어 검정색인 세계 여행 가방 샘플 제작이 지연되고 있음을 알 수 있다."}, {"n": 193, "q": "When is the deadline for Ms. Pereira to approve samples?", "opts": ["May 25", "June 11", "July 20", "August 1"], "ans": 1, "note": "페레이라 씨가 샘플을 승인해야 하는 마감일은? 6월 11일까지 모든 표지 승인을 보내주면 7월 20일 전에 제본된 공책 전체 주문을 발송할 수 있다고 했으므로 (B) 6월 11일이 정답."}, {"n": 194, "q": "What does the form indicate about the Bun Bun Books order?", "opts": ["It will include a display stand.", "It will ship overnight.", "It will be paid upon delivery.", "It will arrive late."], "ans": 0, "note": "양식에서 번번 북스 주문에 대해 명시하는 것은? 고객 이름은 번번 북스, 제품 설명란에 대형 금속 진열대가 표기되어 있어 주문 목록 중 진열대가 포함되어 있음을 알 수 있으므로 (A) 진열대가 포함될 것이다가 정답."}, {"n": 195, "q": "What is the background color on the cover of item N3-GT?", "opts": ["Blue", "Black", "Yellow", "White"], "ans": 0, "note": "항목 N3-GT의 표지 배경 색상은? N3-GT는 위대한 생각들(Great Thoughts)의 표지 디자인이고 첫 이메일에서 그 배경 색상이 파랑(Blue)임을 알 수 있으므로 (A) 파랑이 정답."}]}, {"title": "Questions 196-200 refer to the following e-mail, review, and notice.", "passage": "To: Managers\nFrom: Charlotte Black\nDate: August 16\nSubject: Employee of the month\n\nDear Managers,\n\nIt is time to vote for the Wilson Autos Employee of the Month for September. Here are the nominees.\n\nErica Boyd has been with us for only a few months but has already shown great promise and is eager to learn new things.\n\nLauren Almahdi is very proactive. If something needs to be done, she will point it out to a manager and volunteer to take care of it herself.\n\nNick Salehi found a glitch in our computer system and stopped us from incorrectly ordering unnecessary inventory (thus saving us money).\n\nMax Rhodes has been especially helpful with training new hires. He is calm and patient and explains our procedures well.\n\nPlease respond to this e-mail by Friday with your vote. The winner must receive at least three votes. The winner will be posted at our front desk and on our Web site next Monday.\n\nThanks,\n\nCharlotte Black\nGeneral Manager, Wilson Autos\n\nhttps://www.westchesterreviews.com\n\nWilson Autos (Westchester)\n\n★★★★★\n\nMy wife and I just bought a new Excelera truck at the Wilson Autos Westchester location with the help of Erica Boyd. Even though she was new, she was very knowledgeable about all the trucks on the lot that we wanted to test drive. The few questions she was unable to answer were quickly addressed by her mentor, Max. We were very pleased with the customer service and even more delighted when the general manager agreed to sell us the Excelera for the same price that a competing dealership was advertising. I highly recommend Wilson Autos if you are in the market for a new vehicle!\n\n—Henry Riggs, August 22\nThe employee of the month for September is ERICA BOYD!\n\nIn her three months at Wilson Autos, Erica has picked up new skills quickly and is always trying to learn more. She has become very knowledgeable about our inventory and is able to share her knowledge with customers to complete sales. She has also been instrumental in encouraging satisfied customers to post comments on our social media pages. We received more great reviews in the past month than we did in the four previous months combined!\n\nErica has received a $50 gift card to Alonzo's Restaurant as a thank-you for her excellent work. Congratulations, Erica!", "qs": [{"n": 196, "q": "What is the purpose of the e-mail?", "opts": ["To share a list of job candidates", "To ask for opinions from managers", "To summarize a managers' meeting", "To nominate a manager for an award"], "ans": 1, "note": "(공지) 9월 윌슨 오토의 이달의 직원에게 투표할 시간이며, 금요일까지 여러분의 투표를 이 이메일로 회신해 달라는 관리자 셜럿 블랙의 안내."}, {"n": 197, "q": "According to the e-mail, who identified a technical problem?", "opts": ["Mr. Salehi", "Ms. Almahdi", "Mr. Rhodes", "Ms. Black"], "ans": 0, "note": "닉 살레히는 우리 컴퓨터 시스템에서 오류를 발견하고 불필요한 재고를 잘못 주문하는 것을 멈춰 주어 비용을 절약해 주었다는 추천 내용."}, {"n": 198, "q": "What can be concluded about Mr. Riggs?", "opts": ["His previous vehicle was an Excelera truck.", "He is a neighbor of Ms. Boyd's.", "He has purchased a vehicle from Wilson Autos in the past.", "He negotiated with Ms. Black for a lower price."], "ans": 3, "note": "후기: 윌슨 오토 웨스트체스터 지점에서 에리카 보이드의 도움을 받아 신형 엑셀러라 트럭을 구입. 총괄 관리자가 경쟁 대리점에서 광고하는 동일가로 엑셀러라를 판매하기로 동의해 더욱 기뻤다. 헨리 릭스, 8월 22일."}, {"n": 199, "q": "What is indicated in the notice about Ms. Boyd?", "opts": ["She eats regularly at Alonzo's Restaurant.", "She manages social media sites for Wilson Autos.", "She is responsible for an increase in customer feedback.", "She recently completed a sales training course."], "ans": 2, "note": "(공지) 에리카는 만족한 고객들이 소셜 미디어 페이지에 의견을 남기도록 하는 데 중요한 역할을 했고, 지난 한 달 동안 이전 4개월 합친 것보다 더 많은 훌륭한 후기를 받았다."}, {"n": 200, "q": "What is most likely true about Ms. Boyd?", "opts": ["She received votes from at least three managers.", "She was the top salesperson in August.", "She has years of experience in the auto industry.", "She was hired by Wilson Autos in April."], "ans": 0, "note": "9월 이달의 직원은 에리카 보이드. 공지에서 수상자는 최소 3표 이상을 받아야 한다고 했으며, 후기에서 에리카가 다수의 긍정적 후기를 이끌어냈음을 알 수 있어 그녀가 수상자로 선정됨."}]}]};
